<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5602] Add cache access pattern statistics and report hot blocks/keys</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5602</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In many practical applications it would be very useful to know how well utilized the block cache is, i.e. how many times we actually access a block once it gets into cache. This would also allow to evaluate cache-on-write on flush. In addition, we need to keep track of and report some set of hottest block in cache, and possibly even hottest keys. This would allow to diagnose &quot;hot-row&quot; problems in real time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
