                            <comment id="13233101" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 20 Mar 2012 01:33:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;An alternative cache metric that would be interesting to know is the last access time of the entries being evicted. If the last-access-time is only a minute or so, it&apos;s likely that you can benefit from adding more cache. If it&apos;s substantially older, then adding cache won&apos;t really help. &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five-minute_rule&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five-minute_rule&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
